⍝ This is actually a pretty difficult problem in Kap. Not because
⍝ it's hard to solve, but because this kind of array manipulation
⍝ is so fundamental to the language that it's hard to define what
⍝ it means to not use the native reverse function, which is
⍝ just a single character in Kap.
⍝
⍝ The following code computes a reverse number sequcence and uses
⍝ it to look up the characters in the original array.

solve ⇐ { ⍵[(¯1+≢⍵)-⍳≢⍵] }

io:println solve "reverse the given string"
